;; ===========================================================================
;; §1 — WHAT LANDED
;; ===========================================================================

  :executive-summary
"Both authoring lanes (books + graph seed) landed clean earlier today. I
executed the fold-and-fire per the plan:

  1. Extracted 1,939 candidate pairs from 16 edited books + 14 graph nodes.
  2. Applied 7-technique fold (LIMA/LIMO/LASER/LIFT/DEITA/LIMR/MIG) →
     1,507 selected pairs after quality/provenance/dedupe/diversify.
  3. Merged v3 train (89,956) + v4 selected (1,507) → v4 train 91,463.
     Preserved v3 valid.jsonl (9,916) and heldout.jsonl (1,000) UNCHANGED.
  4. Signed v4 manifest (ed25519, cortex@motoi) — verified.
  5. Wrote v4 training config (seed 37, iters 45,732, otherwise identical
     to v2.0 config per lock).
  6. Fired training via forge-fire.sh — PID 96119, first val loss 2.976
     at iter 1, training LR ramping through warmup as expected.

Corpus delta: +1,507 pairs added to train (+1.7%). Under the plan's
2,135 estimate because per-section extraction yielded fewer USE pairs than
projected (many book sections lack code fences). Under the plan's grand
total 3,335 because subsystem-limit graph seed emitted 207 selected pairs
rather than the ~1,200 projected (12 sample-instructions × 14 nodes = 168
raw sample-instruction pairs; the 5-element decomposition added ~57 more
per-node before DEITA culling). Fold quality > raw count — every pair
traces to a specific book heading or graph-node element.

Reveal Mk C should probe the 45,732-iter adapter after training completes."

