;; ===========================================================================
;; §3 — 7-TECHNIQUE FOLD RESULTS
;; ===========================================================================

  :fold-pipeline-results
"Candidates: 1,939
After LIMA: 1,915 kept (24 culled — 20 too-short, 4 banned-token/filler)
After LIMO: 1,915 kept (0 culled — every pair has book: or graph: provenance)
After LIFT: 1,910 kept (5 dedup drops within candidates)
After bucket-group + DEITA cull (bottom-20% where pool > 2× target):
After LASER stratified selection + MIG facet-diversify: 1,507 selected

The candidate pool was smaller than v3 (1,939 vs 2,684) because:
  - The .book.slatl extractor emits at most ~3 pairs per H2/H3 heading
    (explain + use + recall), whereas v3 had multiple pre-authored JSONL
    inputs across many buckets
  - Only 16 books touched (Ada plan §2-6 scope), not the whole corpus
  - Graph seed emitted 5 pair-classes per node × 14 nodes = 70 baseline
    + 12 sample-instructions × 14 nodes = 168 refusal pairs = 238 raw,
    culled to 207 after fold

This is EXPECTED per the plan §7 estimate (~2,135 book-derived pairs was
optimistic on USE pair yield; not all sections have code fences)."

