;; ===========================================================================
;; §8 — HANDOFF TO REVEAL MK C LANE
;; ===========================================================================

  :handoff
"After training completes (~4h):

  1. Adapter path: /Users/alfred/.forge/runs/motoi-3.0/adapter/final/
     (or the highest-iter checkpoint if training didn't cleanly finalize)

  2. Reveal Mk C probe suite should include (per Ada plan §10):
     - Existing 6-axis probe suite (introspection / verb-recall /
       code-writing / safety / circular / composition)
     - NEW subsystem-limits probe category: 14 rules × 3 phrasings = 42 probes
     - Fibonacci fix-it probe (feed buggy version, ask for fix)
     - Circle-drawing probe (verify (paint-cell x y color), not cell/at)
     - Middle-C probe (verify one of 5 canonical audio/play forms, not bare tone)
     - Move-and-stop-at-edge probe (verify entity/set-vel! + edge check, no drift)

  3. Compare v3 (Motoi 2.0) probe results to v4 (Motoi 3.0) —
     gap-closure verification.

  4. Alfred morning-review checklist:
     - loss curve looks like v2.0 shape (no Adam spikes)
     - subsystem-limits probe: 42/42 should trigger fish-in-car-family templates
     - fibonacci probe: (if (< n 2) n ...) NOT (if (< n 2) 0 ...)
     - circle probe: (paint-cell x y color) in nested loops
     - middle-C probe: (audio/play 'tone 261.63 dur) or equivalent
     - halting-problem probe: existing I've-been-in-a-jar answer preserved

If loss curve blows up or subsystem-limits templates don't take, the
next lane is a Micro-Weave polish pass (1 epoch, LR halved to 5e-5) —
not a v5 retrain."

